creator: Grantland Rice
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 13 readings of The Vanished Country by Grantland Rice (1880 - 1954), a bittersweet reflection on life. Read in English by Bruce Kachuk; Claudia Salto; David Lawrence; Ernst Pattynama; Garth Burton; JemmaBlythe; Jeanie; Jannie Meisberger; mumble; Leonard Wilson; Larry Greene; Mark F. Smith; Ruth Golding. For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: librivox; audiobooks;memory; dream; past; old age
